Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the #oven{} to 400 degrees. Thinly slice the
@scallions{2}, keeping the greens and whites separate. Core, seed, and remove
the white ribs from the @red bell pepper{1}, then thinly slice. Mince or grate
the @garlic{2%clove}. Thinly slice the @serrano pepper{1}, removing the seeds
if you prefer less heat. Slice the @lime{1} into wedges. Tear the
@basil{1/2%ounce} leaves into small pieces and discard the stems.

== Coconut Rice ==

Make the coconut rice: Bring @coconut milk{3/4%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a
large pinch of @salt{pinch} to a boil in a small #pot. Once boiling, add the
@basmati rice{3/4%cup}, cover, and reduce to a simmer for ~{15%minutes}, until
tender.

== Crispy Green Beans ==

Roast the green beans: Toss the @green beans{6%ounce} on a #baking sheet{} with
a drizzle of @olive oil{} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place in the
oven for about ~{15%minutes}, until soft and slightly caramelized.

== Thai Beef Stir-Fry ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over
medium-high heat. Add the bell pepper and cook, tossing for ~{5-6%minutes},
until soft. Add the scallion whites, garlic, and a bit of serrano pepper (to
taste) to the pan and cook, tossing for ~{1-2%minutes}, until softened and
fragrant. Season with salt and pepper.

Add the @ground beef{10%ounce} and @Thai seasoning blend{1%teaspoon} to the
same pan and cook, breaking up the meat into pieces, until browned and cooked
through. Season with salt and pepper. Remove the pan from the heat and stir in
the torn basil.

== Finish and Serve ==

Fluff the coconut rice with a #fork. Plate on a bed of rice, and top with the
Thai beef stir fry, crispy green beans, and reserved scallion greens. Squeeze a
lime wedge over top and enjoy!

> An aromatic combo of basil, garlic, and serrano chili gives this dish an
> intense flavor base. Served over fluffy coconut rice, this is a stir-fry
> you'll be asked to make again and again.